reference:
Manson JE, et al. 2018. Marine n-3 Fatty Acids and Prevention of
Cardiovascular Disease and Cancer. NEJMoa1811403.
doi:10.1056/NEJMoa1811403.
description:
Description
The results summarize each of the health outcomes for an experiment where
12,933 subjects received a 1g fish oil supplement daily and 12,938 received
a placebo daily.  The experiment's duration was 5-years.
title: Findings on n-3 Fatty Acid Supplement Health Benefits

parameters.invasive_cancer_after_2y: Invasive cancer of any type, excluding the first 2 years of follow-up.
parameters.cancer_death_after_2y: Death from cancer, excluding the first 2 years of follow-up.
parameters.myocardial_infarction_after_2y: Total myocardial infarction, excluding the first 2 years of follow-up.
parameters.cardio_event_expanded: Cardiovascular event in expanded composite endpoint.
parameters.death_after_2y: Death from any cause, excluding the first 2 years of follow-up.
parameters.major_cardio_event_after_2y: Major cardiovascular event, excluding the first 2 years of follow-up.
parameters.invasive_cancer: Invasive cancer of any type. (Primary end point.)

format:
The format is a list of 24 matrices.  Each matrix is a 2x2 table,
and below are the named items in the list, which also represent the
outcomes.
